\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus closed his eyes and pushed out with his mana sense until it encompassed the entire room. He sank into a semi-meditative state, with full consciousness directed onto the mana surrounding him. Within a few breaths he felt five intense points blaze into being within the room, each point coalesced into a brilliant sphere of aspected mana about 15 cm in diameter. The spheres drifted on the ambient mana moving lazily about the room rather than remaining fixed in place.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 [Quickly Marcus reached out and touched each sphere with his senses one by one. The first was like touching a red hot burner on a stove. It wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t fire mana, though. It was something more than just heat or flames\u8230\'85 something brighter and sharper. It was radiant affinity mana! The next was sphere was easier, it tasted of ozone, like touching your tongue to a battery. Lightning affinity, definitely. The third was solid and felt like running his fingers through rich loam soil. Earth affinity, which meant he needed to keep it away from the lightning sphere or they would likely explode, discharging all of their mana violently. The fourth sphere was solid and strong, with a sense of\u8230\'85 being almost unstoppable. Force affinity, he was sure of it, which meant that sphere probably couldn\u8217\'92t be affected by any other sphere in the room. And the last sphere was cold, dark and hungry trying to absorb every bit of mana it encountered. Dark affinity, which made the whole thing complicated since Dark affinity would consume anything.] [How the heck does he know all this?]}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 With some gentle nudging from his Mana Control skill, he positioned the spheres around the room, keeping them separated and preparing for the stream to start. As he felt the mana stream begin pouring into the room, Marcus erected two barriers one of dark mana around the dark sphere and one of force mana around himself. Only dark mana could pass through the dark barrier, keeping that sphere from consuming anything but the stream of dark mana he would need to set up.  The force mana would block any mana from reaching him while he got his mana streams organized.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mentally, he grabbed hold of the incoming mana stream, using his will to pass it through a sieve. He used the sieve to break the stream into its component parts, then began directing the individual streams to the correct spheres. Once he managed that, he infused each stream with yet more of his will, causing each of the streams to begin attracting mana of the same affinity. This caused each stream to begin slurping up any loose mana of its own type and drag that mana along with it into the sphere.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Once that was finally stabilized, he turned to the final part of the problem, dissipating the barrier around himself. Then he began breathing in the mana that was not part of his streams or being attracted by them, cycling that mana through his core and purifying it. As soon as he was sure he had everything moving correctly, he relaxed a little. The difficulty here was setting up the flows and keeping the sieve in place. Maintaining it was like keeping six free-spinning wheels in motion, a quick touch here and there to keep anything from slowing or stopping and everything was good. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 After a small eternity of juggling the mana streams, the incoming flow began to diminish, signaling an end to the flood. This was the final tricky part, as the flow behind the streams began to slacken, risking it all falling apart. So he moved on to his endgame, wrapping each stream with the a thick layer of mana that he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d stripped all the affinities from. He infused this unaspected mana with a sense of solidness to prevent it from being consumed by the aspected mana and used it squeeze the streams. It felt very much like rolling up an almost empty tube of toothpaste to make sure none was wasted.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 As the last of the mana from the streams was absorbed, he collapsed the dark mana barrier around it\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s sphere and let the sphere consume that mana as well before opening his eyes on his System notifications.}
