\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Marcus took a few deep breaths before turning his eyes to the Guide. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Now what?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Now I help you evolve your Basic Meditation skill,\u8221\'94 she replied. \u8220\'93Begin by entering meditation, but try to split your focus to include my voice. If I have to intrude on you mentally to instruct you it will be more difficult.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 He closed his eyes and sank into his meditation, falling into the flow of his mana while forcing himself to also listen to the world around him. It took several minutes of effort for him to become aware of sound without losing his focus on his mana. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Good, very good,\u8221\'94 he heard the Guide speak softly from what seemed like a great distance. \u8220\'93Now, instead of following the mana through your pathways, try to widen your focus like you did when you spread your senses through the test chamber. Try to feel all of your mana at once. Instead of becoming part of the flow, become one with the entire flow.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Part of Marcus boggled at the thought. How was he supposed to become one with his mana? He had learned to follow the mana flows by imagining himself as a leaf carried along on a stream, something his conscious mind could wrap itself around to anchor it within the flow. But to become the flow? That was something else entirely. He cast around for a way to conceptualize it. Something he could comprehend\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The idea hit him suddenly, dissolution! He flowed the stream until he reached his core once more and instead of continuing onward, he submerged himself in the core, feeling the energy coursing around him. He pictured himself slowly dissolving like sugar in tea. Melting and diffusing through his core. Being spread throughout his pathways by the flow until there was no part of his mana flow that he wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t in. The feeling was intense and overwhelming at first. He struggled to both retain his sense of self and his diffuse state simultaneously. He groped through the sensation centimeter by centimeter, moment by moment until he began to understand. Until he finally realized he had infused his will, his intent, into the entire stream. It was no longer something alien to his soul, it was mere another part of him, like an arm or a leg. He could manipulate every part of it as if it were merely another set of muscles. }
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Of course, like any set of muscles that had never been exercised, it was weak. He would need time and practice to exercise those muscles. To grow [stronger] and exert meaningful control. If he ever wanted to push his mana compression further, he would need for this particular \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93muscle\u8221\'94 to get much, much [stronger.] And so he began, squeezing the entire system with all of his currently feeble might, then relaxing. He repeated this process again and again. He kept at it until a deep throbbing ache began to build in his awareness and he realized just how fatigued his consciousness felt.}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\tx360\tx720\tx1080\tx1440\tx1800\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\fi360\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Crap! He realized that he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d expended all the mental energy he\u8217\'92d had left on this process and began pulling himself back together. Concentrating his awareness back into a singular consciousness. Thankfully, that turned out to be easier than he feared given his exhausted state. Finally he opened his eyes blearily and crawled back into his bedroll before passing out. }}